fastqc: used for performing quality control on raw throughput seq data.
        * import BAM (Binary Alignment/Map)**compressed SAM(Sequence Alignment/Map)**human readable or FastQ files and lines start with '@'
        * provide overview to tell which ares may have problems
        * example comand : 
          module avail fastqc # is it downloaded
          module load fastqc # load it if its not
          fastqc <file>.fastq # run fastqc
          
Alignment to Reference: align sequence to a reference genome 
        * Tools: BWA
        * example command:
          module avail bwa 
          module load bwa
          bwa mem hg(37/38).fa <file>.fastqc > aln-pe.sam
          
Samtools: used to analize and manipualt files in SAM/DAM format
        * convert sam fle to BAM files:
            module avail samtools #check available versions
            module load samtools/1.13 #load specific version
        * sort BAM files
            samtools view aln-pe.sam -b | samtools sort > aln-pe.bam
            samtools index aln-pe.bam #
        * index BAM file:
            ls -lh aln-pe.sam
            ls -lh aln-pe.bam
Picard: Used to manipulate and modify SAM files and remove duplicates
       * example comand:
       module avail picard
       module load picard-tools/2.8.1

       PicardCommandLine MarkDuplicates I=aln-pe.bam O=marked_duplicates.bam
       M=marked_dup_metrics.txt

       PicardCommandLine AddOrReplaceReadGroups I=marked_duplicates.bam
       O=marked_duplicates.RG.bam RGID=1 RGLB=lib1 RGPL=illumina RGPU=unit1 RGSM=3

Sumit a job:
       nano bash.picard.sh #make file
       sbatch bash.picard.sh 

       squeue -u <UNIQ_NAME> # check the job running
       less slurm-<job_id>.out # check the output

       samtools view aln-pe.bam -f 0x400| wc -l #use samtools to view and check duplicates marked by picard
       samtools view marked_duplicates.RG.bam -f 0x400 |wc -l
       
       
